cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper belongs to the field of natural language processing and machine learning, specifically in the area of corpus extraction and machine translation evaluation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) in the process of extracting data from Wikipedia, and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) in the development of the toolkit. Additionally, the paper touches on issues of gender and diversity (cs.CY) in the creation of a gender-balanced corpus.
